# ============================================
# ADMIN DASHBOARD CONFIGURATION
# ============================================

# Backend API base URL
# Point this at the backend origin (not /api path)
# Development: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://api.yourdomain.com
VITE_API_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# ============================================
# NOTES
# ============================================

# Development Setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
# 2. Update VITE_API_URL to match your backend URL
# 3. Ensure backend has ADMIN_FRONTEND_URL set in its .env
# 4. Run: bun install
# 5. Start dev server: bun run dev (runs on http://localhost:5174)

# Backend Configuration Required:
# The backend must include this admin dashboard URL in:
# - CORS allowed origins (ADMIN_FRONTEND_URL in backend/.env)
# - Better Auth trusted origins (automatically included via ALLOWED_ORIGINS)
# 
# Example backend/.env:
#   FRONTEND_URL="http://localhost:5173"
#   ADMIN_FRONTEND_URL="http://localhost:5174"

# Access Requirements:
# - User must have ADMIN or SUPER_ADMIN role in database
# - Promote users with: cd ../backend && bun run admin:promote user@example.com
# - Or create test admin: cd ../backend && bun run admin:promote --create admin@test.com password123
# - Login via: http://localhost:5174 → Sign In with StreamIt Account

# Production Setup:
# - Set VITE_API_URL to production backend URL (must use HTTPS)
# - Ensure backend CORS allows admin dashboard origin
# - Set ADMIN_FRONTEND_URL in backend production .env
# - Use secure session cookies (httpOnly, secure, sameSite)
# - Deploy to separate subdomain (e.g., admin.yourdomain.com)
# - Consider IP whitelisting or VPN access for additional security

# Features:
# - User management and suspension
# - Creator application review
# - Content moderation (posts, comments, streams)
# - Financial operations (withdrawals, transactions)
# - Ad campaign management
# - Legal compliance (takedowns, geo-blocks)
# - System settings and announcements
# - Audit history and permissions
